column5: Just found this on the web...this is bigger than the sunfish I used to catch off my friend's dock up north....LOL.
WOW! It is a shame for them that it is nearly inedible..But would they still call this sunfish a pan-fish?
Now we gotta find a big stove....this will do I think....LOL
Perfect Cliff.  I'll meet you here when its done:    (come on its way to nice for anyone to be expected to get work done in the office - google images will have to do!)
LOL...that's exactly what I did to find the stove (gotta love google images)....let me know when it's done...I think there's enough for the whole family....
Cool!!  I'll be there in a minute, I'll bring this.    Joey
..What no beer with that fish.that is a huge one.  Steve
In anticipation of next year's OFC tourney for the "Ocean Panfish" category...  Preparing for my Gaza Strip fishin' getaway:
Imagine the pike that would eat the sunfish down there...ah yes, but they are also largely inedible due to the enormous y-bones
Lets just hope there no C4 inside of that thing.
